cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on intelligent surveillance system that extracts useful features from frames, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the storage and access of multimedia content, which may require security measures to protect sensitive information. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an intelligent surveillance system that leverages edge computing and provides dynamic response, which falls under the domain of AI. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the indexing and querying of multimedia content, which requires efficient data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the distribution of multimedia content and the use of edge computing, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
